        <title>What is Explicit Instruction?</title>
        <contents>&lt;div style="width: 716px;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width="148" height="340" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="Scaffolded skyscraper with crane" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LTA-EI-S1c-scaffolded.jpg" /&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Explicit instruction is characterized by a series of supports or scaffolds, whereby students are guided through the learning process with clear statements about the purpose and rationale for learning,...clear explanations and demonstrations of the instructional target, and supported practice with feedback until independent mastery has been achieved&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. (Archer &amp;amp; Hughes, 2011,  p. 1)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explicit instruction is: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;structured&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;systematic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;flexible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;responsive to the needs of adult learners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;research-based&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is called &lt;em&gt;explicit&lt;/em&gt; because it is a &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;direct approach&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; to teaching that outlines how to plan and deliver instruction. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let's take a look at each of these characteristics more closely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="color: #993300;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Click on the Next button below to continue.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</contents>
