        <title>Explicit Instruction is....</title>
        <contents>&lt;div style="width: 716px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;img width="150" height="121" style="float: right; border: 1px solid black; margin-left: 5px; margin-right: 5px;" alt="file folders with magnifying glass" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LTA-EI-S1b%20-%20research-based-magnify-folders.jpg" /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research-Based&lt;/strong&gt; - Explicit instruction is a framework of instruction that matches what we know about learning and long term retention of knowledge and skills. EI incorporates many options for helping our learners understand the organization and logic of what they are learning. This helps them &lt;em&gt;hook into &lt;/em&gt;and&lt;em&gt; hold onto&lt;/em&gt; new knowledge and skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
